div.p:
On déduit que 
\begin{eqnarray*}
E_{\lambda_1}& = & \{(x,y,z,t) \in \mathbb{R}^4: x=y+z=0\}\\
& = & \{(x,y,z,t) \in \mathbb{R}^4: y=-z, x=0\}\\
& = & \{(0,-z,z,t): t,z \in \mathbb{R} \}.
\end{eqnarray*}

On déduit que 
\begin{eqnarray*}
E_{\lambda_2}& = & \{(x,y,z,t) \in \mathbb{R}^4: z=y+z+t=x+y+z=0\}\\
& = & \{(x,y,z,t) \in \mathbb{R}^4: z=0, y=-t, x=t\}\\
& = & \{(t,-t,0,t): t \in \mathbb{R} \}.
\end{eqnarray*}
